Deputy Resort Manager
29 Apr 2014 08:39 PM - UAE
. Deputy Resort Manager Company Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide, Inc. is one of the leading hotel and leisure companies in the world with over 1000 properties in more than 100 countries and 155,000 employees at its owned and managed properties. Starwood Hotels is a fully integrated owner, operator and franchisor of hotels and resorts with the following internationally renowned brands: St. RegisŽ, The Luxury CollectionŽ, SheratonŽ, WestinŽ, Four PointsŽ by Sheraton, WŽ, Le MéridienŽ and the recentlyannounced AloftSM and ElementSM Hotels. Starwood Hotels also owns Starwood Vacation Ownership, Inc., one of the premier developers and operators of high quality vacation interval ownership resorts. For more information, please visit www.starwoodhotels.com Location Sheraton Abu Dhabi Hotel & Resort is a landmark in the city for its architecture and its ideal location. Prominently situated on the Abu Dhabi Corniche, featuring a natural lagoon with turquoise clear water leading to the Arabian Gulf, Sheraton Abu Dhabi Hotel & Resort offers not just luxury but is also a place of tranquillity and relaxation.The hotel is within walking distance of the shopping and commercial districts and only 40 minutes drive from the Abu Dhabi International Airport. Department Resort Job Description Support the Resort Manager in running the day to day operation of the resort including the spa and gym. Ensures that the spa, gym, pool and beach are in best condition and cleanliness and hygiene are observed in all areas. Supervises the resort team and relieves the Resort Manager during absence.Welcome and assist the guests and ensure that the facilities offered to guests and members are always in best condition. Assist in handling guest queries and complaints. Assists in conducting training and appraisal to the team. Requirements - College level/Degree holder- With minimum 2 years sales experience in a 5 star hotel
